Dependent questions and dependent exclamatione commonly take the indicative in old Latin (parataxis, the question-clause or exclamation-clause being in form co-ordinate with the principal clause) ε so 572, 614, 626, 104o; exclamatory, 460, 1172. But the subjunctive is also found in Plautus, and not only where it has independent meaning but also in other cases, e.g. 199 and 969, where indic. and subj. stand side by side without any clear logical distinction.
